Nice Talent Asset Management Limited

Nice Talent Asset Management Limited (NTAM) is a fast-growing asset management company with SFC Type 4 and Type 9 licenses. Our team comprised of seasoned bankers and investment advisors from international banks. We are now inviting ambitious talents to take part in the growth of our business.

Junior Analyst Program

We offer a unique opportunity for high caliber and ambitious young talents who aspire to develop their career in asset management industry. You will have the opportunity to kick-start your career at our company with a well-defined development roadmap. Your on-job training experience will be enriched through a wide range of functions in an asset management firm as we continue to grow our business scale.

Our 2-year Junior Analyst Program is offered in three major function streams: Investment, Operation and Compliance. You will first go through basic training as a junior analyst for the first 6 – 12 months where you will learn about basic operation of an asset management firm. Then you will subsequently rotate through the three different function streams for the rest of the program:

Investment

Work closely with our investment directors in identifying investment opportunities in a wide range of asset classes i.e. Equities, Fixed income, FX, etc.;
Asset and support investment directors in monitoring investment portfolio and product development;
Provide timely market update for our bankers / clients;
Conduct fundamental research with ultimate goal of generating tradable ideas

Operation

Perform pre-trade / post-trade checking with our counterparties;
Perform back-office function on managing and monitoring our existing investment portfolio;
Support our bankers with client related tasks such as account reviews, investment proposal generation;
Develop and maintain our internal trade database, systems and various spreadsheets for daily operations

Compliance

Liaise with our external compliance consultant to handle regulatory filings to regulators;
Review, revise and draft internal manuals, policies and procedures to ensure in compliance with rules and regulation of the SFC;
Assist with internal risk monitoring, including but not limited to operational and investment risk monitoring
Assist the team with bank account openings, conduct KYC/AML checking and other necessary investigations

Who are we looking for?

Bachelor degree or above in Economics/ Finance/ Mathematics/ Risk management/ Computer engineering would be preferred but not necessary;
Relevant industry experience is preferred. Recent graduates will also be considered;
Excellent organization and communication skills;
Passion and interest in financial market is a must;
Ability to work under pressure and maintain quality of detailed work while meeting tight deadlines;
Proficient in English, Mandarin and Cantonese;
Knowledge of VBA or any programming language is a plus

Responsibilities:

Responsible for financial analysis and management report with commentary to support strategic business planning and monitor business performance;
Work closely with various internal parties to investigate major variances aim at budgetary controls
Make use of operational and financial data to enhance management reports and/or schedules and drive actions, i.e. cost savings and/or operational efficiencies
Conduct financial modeling, feasibility studies, returns on investments analysis to facilitate business decisions
Assist in Listing rules compliance matters and ad-hoc projects as assigned

Requirements:

Degree holder in Accounting, Finance or equivalent discipline;
Qualifies accountant with HKICPA, ACCA or equivalent designations is preferred;

At least 4 to 5 years of solid audit and/or commercial experience in financial analysis , with electronics product manufacturing or Big 4 experience is an advantage;
Energetic; Strong analytical skills and business acumen;
Proficient in both spoken and written Chinese, Mandarin and English;
Excellent Skills in Excel and Power point application.

